I guess I was a little misled on this. I was expecting the "entire" season to be one big video highlight with music and narration that included the Big Ten Championship, The Sugar Bowl & The National Championship included. This was a short t.v. show interview with Urban along with some highlights of their games. I was disappointed. It just wasn't what I expected and I wouldn't recommend it to anyone. It would have been fine just to see this on t.v. but not to have spent the money for a dvd. A big letdown for me.

ALL YOU  NEED TO KNOW ABOUT THE GREAT SEASON

i see all the negative reviews, I think mostly its people who didn't realize what they were buying. Game Time with Urban Meyer, is the weekly show recapping the game before and talking about the next opponent. It is taped on Thursday or Friday of the week following the previous game. Then it is televised the Saturday morning. This is done to recap last game and get everyone informed and excited about the game later in the day.

If I bought this expecting a season long highlight show and in depth review. I too would be disappointed. Because this is run through Ohio State Football & the athletic department. You are going to get the calls from the Ohio State radio booth, not national TV guys. I hope this review helps everyone understood what it is you are purchasing and if you buy it I believe you can enjoy it a lot because you will know what it is your buying. Have a great day and Go Bucks
